ENTRY            D0403   20260410   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D0403001   20260410   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                 10         21
TITLE      Neutron transition multipole moment for
            88Sr(a,a')88Sr(*)(2+, 1.84 MeV)
AUTHOR     (S.K.Datta, S.Ray, H.Majumdar, S.K.Ghosh, C.Samanta,
           S.Ray, P.Dasgupta, S.N.Chintalapudi, S.R.Banerjee)
INSTITUTE  (3INDSAH)
           (3INDIND) Kalyani University, Kalyani, West Bengal
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,39,1281,1989)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC)
SAMPLE     The target was prepared by reducing natural Sr (NO3)2
            with Al powder and then evaporating it onto a
            20 mu-g/cm2 carbon backing. The target thickness was
            350 mu-g/cm2.
DETECTOR   (SILI) Detectors of 2 mm active thickness were used.
ANALYSIS   A monitor detector was put at 40 degree and absolute
            normalization of the data was obtained by comparing
            the elastic cross section at this angle to an optical
            model fit.
ERR-ANALYS  The error in the absolute cross section ~20%.
HISTORY    (20060728C) SD
           (20260410A) VT. Entry revised. COMMON: DATA-ERR,
            ERR-DIG, ANG-ERR-D deleted
ENDBIB              21
